definition: to cut down/to fell/to dispatch an expedition against/to attack/to boast/Taiwan pr. [fa1]
tree/wood/coffin/wooden/simple/numb/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]

sentences.english: "More than 50 of them used to be my workmates, " added Fan.
sentences.chinese: 他还补充道，“有50多户都曾是我的伐木工友。”

sentences.english: One day three woodcutters climbed the mountain.
sentences.chinese: 一天三伐木工人攀登山。

sentences.english: Two men are chopping away at a log of wood with regular, ringing blows.
sentences.chinese: 两个伐木工人看着一棵树，带着有规律的铃声。

sentences.english: The stretch the villagers have their eye on is also part of a concession.
sentences.chinese: 村民眼馋的林带也属于特许伐木区。

sentences.english: They stopped on the logging road where they met Jesse's, then veered toward the homestead.
sentences.chinese: 它们在伐木路上碰到杰希的脚印后转向了宅基地。

sentences.english: The organization is also paying to train local guides on how to stop theft and illegal tree-cutting.
sentences.chinese: 该组织还支付培训如何制止盗窃和非法伐木当地导游。

sentences.english: Cold stream stripping logging pecking, songbirds Liu Xiao cord quite high.
sentences.chinese: 伐木清溪寒剥啄，鸣禽高柳晓缗蛮。

sentences.english: In Guizhou, logging is undertaken in the forest areas.
sentences.chinese: 在贵州，森林地区的人们从事伐木业。

sentences.english: Finally, the prospect of the development of harvesters in China is suggested.
sentences.chinese: 最后对我国伐木联合机的发展作出了展望。

sentences.english: The lumberjacks carry the logs in their big truck.
sentences.chinese: 伐木工人用大卡车来运送木材。

sentences.english: Lumbering is very importgoodt in some underdeveloped countries.
sentences.chinese: 在一些不旺盛的国家，伐木业十分重要。

sentences.english: We must stop people cuting trees and picking up stones by advice.
sentences.chinese: 我们必须通过劝告的方式阻止人们伐木采石。

sentences.english: A feller, who passed it, took no glance at it.
sentences.chinese: 路过的伐木工人，连看都不看它一眼。

sentences.english: Once a lumbering center, it now has varied industries. Population, 41,882.
sentences.chinese: 曾是一个伐木业中心，如今具有各种各样的工业。

sentences.english: One cold winter's day, Bear went lumbering down to the lake.
sentences.chinese: 一个寒冷的冬天的一天，熊去伐木下到湖边。

sentences.english: The Maine woodsman sits on a stump whose rings number centuries of growth.
sentences.chinese: 缅茵州的伐木人坐在一段有数百年年轮的木桩上。

definition: to chop wood/to chop down trees
bitter work/hard toil/(loanword) coolie, unskilled Chinese laborer in colonial times
